Olympic Air SA cancelled all
scheduled flights on Oct. 19 and Oct. 20 due to a 48-hour strike
by Greek air-traffic controllers, according to an e-mailed
statement today.  The Athens-based carrier said it will add flights on Oct.
18 and Oct. 21 in light of the cancellations, according to the
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
